WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:06.380
Hey, good morning, family. I'm excited to be with you all again today. I was praying and I was asking the Lord.

00:00:06.381 --> 00:00:25.312
I said, 'What do you want me to tell your people?'And he said, 'Brandon, I want you to go back and I want you to tell them again about your incident that happened with your dog, with your daughter.'And I said, 'Okay, well, I can do that.'But it's a very hard story for me to tell.

00:00:25.313 --> 00:00:30.118
It's a pride buster. It's a flesh buster. It's everything for me because of how I acted.

00:00:30.119 --> 00:00:36.155
But the Lord wants you to know that you don't have to be perfect to serve him.

00:00:36.156 --> 00:00:44.880
You don't have to be somebody that is walking around like a holy angel choir singing behind them all the time for God to use them.

00:00:44.881 --> 00:00:50.452
I want you to understand today that it's all by grace. And here's what I did.

00:00:50.453 --> 00:00:58.377
I did something really stupid. My son and I were playing a game.

00:00:58.377 --> 00:01:08.666
It was right after Christmas and we were on Christmas break, and we were playing a game online together and we were just having fun.

00:01:08.667 --> 00:01:17.026
My daughter was playing with the puppy that I got her for Christmas, and it was a small little dog.

00:01:17.027 --> 00:01:24.042
I felt inside before, when she was playing with this dog, I told her, 'Honey, you need to put the dog up. I don't know, you just need to put the dog up.

00:01:24.043 --> 00:01:31.312
Don't let the dog run around by my feet and everything,'because the dog was sitting there nipping at my toes and was just playing around, you know.

00:01:31.313 --> 00:01:38.316
And so I told my daughter, I said, 'You need to put the dog up, honey.'And so I thought she had already obeyed and put the dog up.

00:01:38.317 --> 00:01:47.116
She was sitting there coloring in her coloring book and was over here to my side, but I didn't know that she had put the dog underneath my feet in a blanket.

00:01:47.117 --> 00:02:02.073
And so I jumped up to go to the bathroom real quick because I put the game on pause with my son, and I jumped up and I landed on that dog and I crushed it completely.

00:02:02.075 --> 00:02:18.073
Guts came out the side. Blood was coming out the nose. The dog was shaking profusely, and then all of a sudden, I picked up the dog and I'm looking at it, and the dog just died in my hands because I crushed it.

00:02:18.075 --> 00:02:27.494
So I lost it. I started using bad words. I started yelling at my daughter because of what she did, putting the dog underneath my feet.

00:02:27.495 --> 00:02:37.751
And I just lost it, y'all. I'm embarrassed to say it, but I lost my temper and I shouldn't have done it, you know.

00:02:37.752 --> 00:02:42.866
And so I was screaming at my little girl for not obeying me. I was mad at the situation.

00:02:42.867 --> 00:02:48.531
Bottom line is, I acted a fool. I acted like a total you-know-what. I shouldn't have done it.

00:02:48.532 --> 00:02:52.643
And me, freaking out, I'm screaming and yelling, 'Why did this happen?

00:02:52.644 --> 00:02:58.189
You know, you should have obeyed and you didn't!'And I'm mad at my wife. I'm mad at everybody.

00:02:58.190 --> 00:03:04.119
I'm blaming everybody other than myself for not looking at the dog below because I acted a fool.

00:03:04.120 --> 00:03:10.517
And I'm so upset at the dead dog in my hand, and I was looking at it as a total loss.

00:03:10.518 --> 00:03:17.893
I mean, it's gone. And so I'm like, 'You know what? It is what it is.'So I freaked out.

00:03:17.894 --> 00:03:27.464
And so I took the dog, and my wife had a shoe box, and I said, 'Put that dog in that shoe box and put it out on the porch.

00:03:27.465 --> 00:03:36.514
I don't want to deal with it.'It was because it was cold, and here in Oklahoma, it gets really cold and the ground was frozen, and I knew that there was no way I could dig a hole in the middle of the night.

00:03:36.515 --> 00:03:42.700
It just had snowed and it was freezing cold. So I said, 'Put the dog in the shoe box and put it on the porch.

00:03:42.701 --> 00:03:55.476
I don't want to deal with it right now.'And so my little girl turned to me and she said, 'Daddy, aren't you going to pray for it to be raised from the dead?'And I said, 'Honey, God's not going to hear me when I pray right now for that dog to be raised.

00:03:55.477 --> 00:03:59.263
You pray.'I said, 'I'm not there. You pray.'She said, 'All things are possible to him who believes,'like that to me.

00:03:59.264 --> 00:04:28.087
I told her, 'I'm not there. I just acted out, and the Lord's not going to hear me when I pray.

00:04:28.088 --> 00:04:41.495
You pray.'So, she started marching up and down the hall, just saying, 'All things are possible to him that believes.'And at this time, I left the room because I was so angry.

00:04:41.496 --> 00:04:50.708
I had to get some space. So, I went into our bedroom and I shut the door and I prayed. I asked God—because I lost it so bad.

00:04:50.709 --> 00:04:55.922
And I could hear my little girl up and down the hall, 'In the name of Jesus, get up from the dead!

00:04:55.923 --> 00:05:00.917
In the name of Jesus, get up from the dead!'And needless to say, that dog was dead in that box.

00:05:00.918 --> 00:05:07.031
My wife had put it outside in the cold. It was completely cold outside and everything was frozen.

00:05:07.032 --> 00:05:12.765
And I told her to put it in the trash can or whatever, and I would deal with it in the morning.

00:05:12.766 --> 00:05:21.119
Well, I was praying, and all of a sudden, an hour goes by, two hours go by, and I come back in and I make amends with the family.

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:25.843
And I told them, 'I'm sorry. I just acted a fool. I acted out of anger.

00:05:25.844 --> 00:05:29.740
It was all based out of fear. I was afraid of the loss, afraid of everything.

00:05:29.741 --> 00:05:37.885
I was blaming myself, I was blaming you, and the way I handled it, I'm sorry.'And I apologized, you know, and I took communion over it, and I put it at the foot of Jesus.

00:05:37.886 --> 00:05:41.901
That's where I was. My little girl was still crying, still upset.

00:05:41.902 --> 00:05:50.790
I was holding her at that time, 'Baby, I'm sorry I yelled at you and freaked out at the situation. I'm sorry you lost your dog. We'll replace him.

00:05:50.791 --> 00:05:57.746
But God's got this, you know.'And I was just trying to comfort her, comfort the family because of my actions and everything.

00:05:57.747 --> 00:06:10.356
So, my wife goes, like I said, this is about two hours later. She goes to take the trash out, and I hear her say, 'The dog's gone.

00:06:10.357 --> 00:06:15.833
It wasn't in the shoe box anymore.'So, I thought the raccoons had gotten the dog.

00:06:15.834 --> 00:06:40.879
And so, you know, I'm sitting there, and all of a sudden, she says, 'I hear a squeaking noise.'And it was like, 'Squeak, squeak.'She said, 'I hear a squeaking noise.'She starts looking down, and she sees the dog at the bottom of the trash can, alive, completely alive, begging, wagging its tail, begging to get out of that trash can.

00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:45.800
She goes and tips the trash can over, grabs that dog, and pulls it out.

00:06:45.801 --> 00:06:52.764
God had completely restored all that dog's guts back inside.

00:06:52.765 --> 00:07:08.112
The blood was completely wiped off of it. There were no signs of any kind of trauma on this dog at all. God had completely done a creative miracle on that dog.

00:07:08.113 --> 00:07:17.767
And my wife brought that little puppy in, and it was shivering cold because it was freezing, which is a miracle in itself because of how cold it was.

00:07:17.768 --> 00:07:24.674
And the dog was shaking. And so we put a blow dryer on the dog and started heating that dog up.

00:07:24.675 --> 00:07:30.916
And my little girl was screaming, 'I told you all things are possible to him that believes!

00:07:30.917 --> 00:07:37.074
I told you all things are possible to him that believes, Daddy! I told you he would bring him back!

00:07:37.075 --> 00:07:41.870
I told you he'd bring him back!'because I trained my children to believe the impossible.

00:07:41.871 --> 00:07:50.159
I trained my children to believe that Jesus is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:59.519
And the same Jesus that healed the sick 2,000 years ago even cares about a dog that dies in the bottom of a trash can.

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:08.963
He will even touch your dog. He's no respecter of persons. I believe with all my heart that the faith of a mustard seed can move a mountain.

00:08:08.964 --> 00:08:22.719
I believe even a childlike faith can bring a dog back. All things are possible to him who will believe. And that's what He did that day for her.

00:08:22.720 --> 00:08:41.325
She came down that hall and she's loving that little dog and she's holding it in her hands and she was saying, 'Daddy, I told you all things are possible to him who believes.'And she kept saying it over and over again, just rejoicing and loving that dog and lifting it up in the air and rejoicing because of what God had just done for her.

00:08:41.326 --> 00:08:59.218
When my wife brought that dog in and it was complete—no guts, no blood, no nothing out of his nose, all bones restored, walking around like normal again, all of it completely like nothing had ever happened—it was like a holy hush in my house.

00:08:59.219 --> 00:09:06.677
The presence of the Lord was so strong, and you could feel it. But this is what I want to say to you.

00:09:06.678 --> 00:09:13.004
I had it in my heart, and the Lord told me, and I'll say it again to you all.

00:09:13.005 --> 00:09:34.670
The Lord said this to me: 'Brandon, even on your best day'—because I thought in my mind, this is what I thought, 'Man, if I would have prayed for it, or whatever,'making all these excuses up in my head and talking to him about everything, and I was like, 'Wow!'And he stopped me and he corrected me immediately.

00:09:34.671 --> 00:09:42.517
He said this to me: 'Brandon, even on your best day, son, your righteousness is as filthy rags to me.

00:09:42.518 --> 00:09:51.296
Even on your best day, you cannot earn the anointing. You cannot earn your salvation.

00:09:51.297 --> 00:09:57.999
You cannot earn healing. It's all by grace. I paid the price for you for all of it.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:03.474
And I raised that dog up as a sign and wonder to your little girl.'Do you get that, y'all?

00:10:03.475 --> 00:10:09.059
He brought the dog back, and he did it just for a child. And that's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:10:09.060 --> 00:10:13.041
She was down there, and she prayed. Like I said, that's the way we raise our children.

00:10:13.042 --> 00:10:19.060
We believe with all our heart that Jesus Christ is still doing miracles today.

00:10:19.061 --> 00:10:30.954
And I just want to tell you all, people are always asking me about my faith walk and everything, and I just want to tell you I'm just normal.

00:10:30.955 --> 00:10:34.304
I'm just a normal human being. I've got issues just like everybody else.

00:10:34.305 --> 00:10:41.063
I'm a work in progress. I take one day at a time, and I seek his face every single day.

00:10:41.064 --> 00:10:49.978
I seek him for finances, I seek him to provide for my family as the head of my house, and for better jobs.

00:10:49.979 --> 00:11:03.395
I pray that over us: 'Father, increase our hands so we can be a blessing to your people.'You can't be a real blessing a lot of times if you're broke and making it from paycheck to paycheck, only having enough to pay your bills and borrowing the rest.

00:11:03.396 --> 00:11:08.171
So that's where I'm at. I'm always believing for the supernatural.

00:11:08.172 --> 00:11:12.529
I'm always believing for the impossible, that God is able to do it today.

00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:23.796
I even told you about the time—my son is sitting behind the camera right now—we had another dog that was born dead, completely dead, rigid.

00:11:23.797 --> 00:11:29.316
It was stiff as a board, nasty, coming out green all over. It was nasty.

00:11:29.317 --> 00:11:40.856
And the Lord told me, 'I'm going to start to deal with you with creative miracles, and I'm going to train you through animals.

00:11:40.857 --> 00:11:48.001
I'm going to let you practice this way, and I'm going to train you and teach you how to do these things.'And so, you know what?

00:11:48.002 --> 00:11:56.930
The dog was born dead. And he said, 'Take the dog, brush it off.'And it was purple, it was dead, everything, born that way.

00:11:56.931 --> 00:12:09.919
So, I took the dog in my hand, and I held it there. My son was there, and we were watching it, and he's sitting right by my side.

00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:13.128
I put the dog in my hand, and the Lord said, 'Now, I want to teach you something.

00:12:13.129 --> 00:12:28.684
Speak to the dog and tell it to come back in the name of Jesus and the authority of the name of Jesus.'And so I said, 'In the name of Jesus, I command you to get up.

00:12:28.685 --> 00:12:39.476
In Jesus'name, you will live and not die, and you will come back right now in Jesus'name.'And that dog gasped for air.

00:12:39.477 --> 00:12:54.359
All of a sudden, I felt the power of God come out of my fingers like electricity, and it went into that dead dog's body and the dog's heart—I could feel it start to beat in the palm of my hand.

00:12:54.360 --> 00:13:06.695
And I could feel the lungs start to fill up with air. And all of a sudden, what was a completely purple, lifeless dog started having pink pigment to its skin.

00:13:06.696 --> 00:13:19.074
It started coming back, and everything—the life of all the blood from the heart pumping—started getting everything back alive again right there.

00:13:19.075 --> 00:13:25.111
And my son was sitting there just like he's sitting behind the camera right now; he saw all of it.

00:13:25.112 --> 00:13:40.196
In my amazement, I was just like, 'Oh my gosh, what just happened?'You know, just to see something come back from the dead was a huge deal for me because I believe in God all the time that I'm going to raise people from the dead.

00:13:40.197 --> 00:13:43.439
And I believe with all my heart we're going to do those things.

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:52.150
Signs and wonders will follow those that believe. And I'm telling you all, we are in the last of the last days.

00:13:52.151 --> 00:13:57.675
And a lot of people say, 'Oh, I've heard that before. Jesus isn't coming anytime soon.'Whatever.

00:13:57.676 --> 00:14:04.520
He's coming. I've seen him face to face, and he told me to tell you he's coming, and Jesus is coming.

00:14:04.521 --> 00:14:14.420
And you better get your house right before him, repent, and get your sins all washed in the blood because if you don't, you're going to turn or you're going to burn. And that's the bottom line.

00:14:14.421 --> 00:14:23.111
You're either going to get saved and get right before the Lord, or you're going to get left because the rapture of the church is about to happen, and we're going to get out of here.

00:14:23.112 --> 00:14:31.186
Whether that's 10 years, 20 years, or whatever, that's nothing compared to the 2,000 years that we've been waiting.

00:14:31.187 --> 00:14:40.626
It could be tomorrow. So, you always want to have your lamps full and be seeking him daily instead of just on Sunday.

00:14:40.627 --> 00:14:54.041
You need to have a relationship with the King because Jesus loves you and he wants the best for you, but you're not going to be able to have a part-time relationship with God for a full-time devil.

00:14:54.042 --> 00:15:01.015
You have to have a full-time relationship with God because the devil's not going to be after you just part-time.

00:15:01.016 --> 00:15:05.699
He's going to try to kill, steal, and destroy all the time. That's the kind of devil he is.

00:15:05.700 --> 00:15:11.890
And you may say, 'Well, the devil hasn't been messing with me.'Well, it's probably because you aren't a threat to him.

00:15:11.891 --> 00:15:19.893
You aren't trying to do something to affect his kingdom. And he's not going to sit back idly by and not mess with people who are a threat to him.

00:15:19.894 --> 00:15:35.074
So, you've got to realize you've got to put your armor on today, put your big boy pants on, and go out there and do what God's commissioned you to do: pray for the sick, raise the dead, cast out devils.

00:15:35.075 --> 00:15:42.863
Freely you've been given, freely you give it out. That's the kind of Jesus we serve. He came to save that which was lost.

00:15:42.864 --> 00:15:51.274
And I'm telling you, the greatest harvest of souls that this world has ever seen is yet to happen.

00:15:51.275 --> 00:15:57.106
The greatest outpouring of Joel chapter 2, we're about to see the former and the latter rain together.

00:15:57.107 --> 00:16:08.604
We're about to see great signs and wonders throughout the whole world—seeing arms and legs and eyes and ears popping open, the dead being raised, casting out devils.

00:16:08.605 --> 00:16:13.895
We're going to see some of the greatest miracles this world has ever seen or ever heard of.

00:16:13.896 --> 00:16:18.128
And I'm telling you, it's time to believe for the impossible.

00:16:18.129 --> 00:16:25.403
It's time to achieve the impossible. It's time to believe big. You've got to start believing God for big.

00:16:25.404 --> 00:16:31.168
Stop thinking so small because God wants to be a big God and operate in your life today.

00:16:31.169 --> 00:16:36.683
You have to understand he is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:16:36.684 --> 00:16:40.508
And faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:16:40.509 --> 00:16:47.920
And you've got to believe what he said he would do. You've got to believe it in your heart.

00:16:47.921 --> 00:16:53.409
You've got to cast out the doubt. Say, 'I doubt that doubt, devil. I doubt your doubt.

00:16:53.410 --> 00:16:59.733
I refuse to believe what you're telling me, and I refuse to receive what the enemy's report is.

00:16:59.734 --> 00:17:12.065
I'm going to believe what the Word of God says.'The doctor might tell you you have a day to live, two days to live, whatever, but I know that nothing is impossible to him who believes.

00:17:12.066 --> 00:17:17.279
I know that he'll heal your body and he'll restore you right where you are if you believe him for it.

00:17:17.280 --> 00:17:21.462
He said he cares for even the sparrows, the lily of the field.

00:17:21.463 --> 00:17:29.793
How much more does he care for you? How much more? We're joiners of Jesus. He loves you. Do you understand that?

00:17:29.794 --> 00:17:38.225
Jesus paid the price for you to be free from sickness and disease, from poverty and lack, and from mental torment.

00:17:38.226 --> 00:17:45.380
He paid for it all for you. You don't have to have any of it. Jesus paid the price for you.

00:17:45.381 --> 00:17:53.955
He became a curse for you. Galatians says that Christ has redeemed you from the curse of the law.

00:17:53.956 --> 00:17:57.613
And you've got to speak to your mountain. You've got to speak to your circumstances.

00:17:57.614 --> 00:18:02.984
Faith calls those things that be not as though they were. And you've got to speak to your circumstances.

00:18:02.985 --> 00:18:08.801
That's why you got to live your life. That's what I'm trying to tell you. I teach my children: you got to speak to your mountain.

00:18:08.802 --> 00:18:16.073
And that's what my little girl, even whenever I was broken in that moment, she took on the faith. When my faith was weak, hers was strong.

00:18:16.074 --> 00:18:26.319
She said, "All things are possible to him who believes, Daddy."And that's the way you've got to believe in your life.

00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:34.239
That's the way it is. How big, how bad is your want-to concerning your circumstances to change in your life?

00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:39.304
Your marriage is broke. Your finances are broke. Your house, your children are wayward.

00:18:39.305 --> 00:18:47.565
They're out sleeping around, doing drugs, doing all this bad stuff. How bad is your want-to to change? How bad do you want it?

00:18:47.566 --> 00:18:52.412
Is it bad enough that you get up and you start praying an extra hour early before work?

00:18:52.413 --> 00:18:57.157
Is it bad enough that you get in the word a little bit more at night instead of watching TV?

00:18:57.158 --> 00:19:01.987
How much do you want change in your life? It's not going to just happen.

00:19:01.988 --> 00:19:07.554
You got to feed on the word. Faith cometh by hearing and hearing by the word of God.

00:19:07.555 --> 00:19:15.083
And if you're not getting that word down inside of your heart... When the anointing hits on me, boy, I start crying.

00:19:15.084 --> 00:19:20.980
If you're not getting that word down on the inside of your heart, you're not going to see change.

00:19:20.981 --> 00:19:27.985
You have to eat that word on a day-to-day basis; what I'm telling you is what's going to change your life.

00:19:27.986 --> 00:19:36.453
You have to get it down inside of you. And you got to be strong in the Lord, in the power of his might.

00:19:36.454 --> 00:19:44.671
And the only way you do that is by reading that word, praying, seeking his face, and having a relationship with him.

00:19:44.672 --> 00:19:57.443
That's what's going to set you free. I heard T.D. Jakes say this once: "What do you do when God has become a spare tire that you only use in the time of an emergency?

00:19:57.444 --> 00:20:05.629
And now you are in an emergency and that tire is flat. What do you do?"I heard him say that, and that stuck with me.

00:20:05.630 --> 00:20:12.668
That's the way people are. They only go to God whenever they need something. But if you build a relationship...

00:20:12.669 --> 00:20:21.736
Well, you want to see when God shows up, like he did in our life for that little dog getting up from the dead, creating a miracle.

00:20:21.737 --> 00:20:24.968
Listen to what I'm saying, y'all, I could just see it. It's like an angel out there.

00:20:24.969 --> 00:20:35.279
He was out there going CPR, doing like, putting the guts in there, sewing it up, whatever they do, I don't know, and fixing all that dog up supernaturally.

00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:54.797
But that miracle came out of a birthing of a relationship from a little girl that has been taught since she's been in diapers: living by faith, living by the impossible, believing for the impossible, speaking to your mountain, learning these things, speaking in tongues.

00:20:54.798 --> 00:20:58.783
She's been baptized in the Holy Ghost, praying in tongues since she was three years old.

00:20:58.784 --> 00:21:04.487
Since she's been just barely talking, she's been walking around praying in the Holy Ghost.

00:21:04.488 --> 00:21:09.939
I've been teaching her because she mocks me. So my son, all of us, we all pray in the Holy Ghost.

00:21:09.940 --> 00:21:18.770
We are all seeking him because that's what we do as a family. And so I'm going to encourage you: bring your family up this way.

00:21:18.771 --> 00:21:25.753
Teach them that Jesus will do it. And when you start believing that way, it'll start manifesting in your house.

00:21:25.754 --> 00:21:30.719
God starts showing up big in your home when you start believing for big.

00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:35.359
If you believe small, you'll get small. If you believe big, it's got to be big.

00:21:35.360 --> 00:21:41.288
That's the kind of God we serve. So, I just want to encourage you all today to believe big.

00:21:41.289 --> 00:21:48.415
These are the last days. Jesus is coming. And I'm telling you all, he's coming sooner than what you all think.

00:21:48.416 --> 00:21:57.421
People mock all the time: "Oh, well, I've heard that before."I'm telling you, he told me to come on YouTube and tell my people I'm coming.

00:21:57.422 --> 00:22:01.895
And that's what I'm here to tell you all: Jesus is coming and he loves you.

00:22:01.896 --> 00:22:07.113
So let me pray for you all right now, and we'll close this thing out.

00:22:07.114 --> 00:22:12.451
Father, in the name of Jesus, I thank you, Father, for the word.

00:22:12.452 --> 00:22:17.985
I thank you, Father, for your word is alive in us and sharper than any two-edged sword.

00:22:17.986 --> 00:22:29.211
I thank you, Lord, that the anointing of the Holy Ghost dwells on the inside of us, that we have authority over the devil, and nothing shall by any means hurt us.

00:22:29.212 --> 00:22:38.994
Greater is he that is in us than he that is in the world. A thousand shall fall at our side and 10,000 at our right hand, but it shall not come nigh.

00:22:38.995 --> 00:22:45.333
I thank you, Lord, for your covering over every single one of us, that we're always in the right place at the right time.

00:22:45.334 --> 00:22:52.399
We're joined up with Jesus Christ. We're seated with him in the heavenlies far above all principalities and powers and might.

00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:57.479
